Constructor Detail

DynamicTable

public DynamicTable(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object columnModel,
                    DataObjectList dataList,
                    com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean hideDeleteAndAdd)
Creates a Dynamic Table

Parameters:
columnModel - This parameter determines the columns that the dynamic table will display. It can either be a string which specifies the full name of a metadata document or metadata data structure, or a MetadataDocument (metadata document), or a Document instance, or a DataStructure instance, or a DynamicDocument instance
dataList - DataObjectList of Document instances or DataStructure instances or DynamicDocument instances the list of objects in the DataObjectList, especially in the case of DynamicDocuments, should be of the same metadata type as the type given in the columnModel parameter. In addition, for DynamicDocument instances, they should all have the same ordering of leaf data and leaf count as the type given in the columnModel parameter. Otherwise, the table will display incorrect data under the appropriate table column.
hideDeleteAndAdd - Whether the table will provide delete markers in the first column of the table that provides deletion functionality of the row and the Add row button
Throws:
Will - throw an exception if the columnModel parameter is of incorrect type.
